  "informal_statement": "For every real x ≥ 2, ∑_{p≤x} log p / p ≤ log 4 · (1 + log(x/2)).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Combine the Abel identity for ∑ log p / p with the Chebyshev upper bound θ(t) ≤ t log 4 in both the boundary term and the integral, then integrate 1/t in closed form.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem prime_log_div_sum_upper :\n    ∀ x : ℝ, 2 ≤ x →\n      ∑ p ∈ Finset.Icc 1 ⌊x⌋₊ with p.Prime, Real.log p / (p:ℝ)\n        ≤ Real.log 4 * (1 + Real.log (x / 2))",
